thoughts.reasoning_problem:

Question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? 1984 is printed text.
Options: A) True B) False C) Uncertain
raw_logic_programs:
Predicates:
Digital(x) ::: x is a digital media.
Analog(x) ::: x is an analog media.
Printed(x) ::: x is a printed text.
Streaming(x) ::: x is a streaming service.
Hardcover(x) ::: x is a hardcover book.
Premises:
∀x (Digital(x) → ¬Analog(x)) ::: No digital media are analog.
∀x (Printed(x) → Analog(x)) ::: Every printed text is analog.
∀x (Streaming(x) → Digital(x)) ::: All streaming services are digital.
∀x (Hardcover(x) → Printed(x)) ::: If an object is a hardcover book then it is printed text.
(Streaming(1984) → Hardcover(1984)) ::: If 1984 is a streaming service, then 1984 is a hardcover book.
Conclusion:
Printed(1984) ::: 1984 is printed text.

Digital(x) ::: x is a digital media.
Analog(x) ::: x is an analog media.
Printed(x) ::: x is a printed text.
Streaming(x) ::: x is a streaming service.
Hardcover(x) ::: x is a hardcover book.
Premises:
∀x (Digital(x) → ¬Analog(x)) ::: No digital media are analog.
∀x (Printed(x) → Analog(x)) ::: Every printed text is analog.
∀x (Streaming(x) → Digital(x)) ::: All streaming services are digital.
∀x (Hardcover(x) → Printed(x)) ::: If an object is a hardcover book then it is printed text.
(Streaming(1984) → Hardcover(1984)) ::: If 1984 is a streaming service, then 1984 is a hardcover book.
Conclusion:
Printed(1984) ::: 1984 is printed text.

thoughts.reasoning_problem:
Context: No digital media are analog. Every printed text is analog. All streaming services are digital. If an object is a hardcover book then it is printed text. If 1984 is a streaming service, then 1984 is a hardcover book.
Question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? 1984 is printed text.
Options: A) True B) False C) Uncertain
